The paper deals with image synthesis using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of soft masks to preserve the semantic layout of the content image is a novel approach that involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a generative Markov random field (MRF) model, which is a common tool in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
